Develop a sketch that **visualizes the trace of multiple objects**. Experiment with various [types of motion](https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1aoUH6oCXzESZsXHGy_0lFHGd8DnE81QKhXwcv4QYauU/edit?usp=sharing) and **Dynamic Arrays**. Utilize [vectors](https://p5js.org/reference/#/p5.Vector) and **vector math functions** in p5.js.

Focus on drawing **Traces** utilizing **diverse movement** and (slow) **velocity.** (Plus, acceleration (deceleration)\!)

- Develop a **Class** by utilizing the **p5.Vector** and **vector math** functions.
- Focus on the **movement** of the objects.
- Explore with **acceleration**\!
- Apply **vector functions** to manipulate **properties**.
  - Use vector addition, subtraction multiplication, division and/or other vector functions to manipulate the magnitude and direction of the movement.

## **Requirements**

- The Class should be declared in the **ES6 Model**.
  - ES6 Model: **`class Ball { … }`**
  - Classical Model: **`function Ball() { … }`**
- The object(s) should include at least **three methods** (functions; they are the object's actions and/or behaviors).
- **Limit the number of objects** and control the number of objects with the property, **`isDone`**, and/or the **lifespan** concept.
- Using **transformations** in the display() function is **highly** encouraged.
- Having user interaction is optional.
